The paper focuses on the use of unsupervised machine learning to analyze data on human interactions in immersive simulations, with the goal of helping teachers understand the effects of student actions on system dynamics. This suggests a strong focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of interpretability in machine learning models, which is a topic of interest in the cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
